--              3-bit input vectors built from consecutive index digit pairs
--              (mod 8 for 3-bit range):
--                  2   -> "010"  Y = "00000100" (Y2)
--                  4   -> "100"  Y = "00010000" (Y4)
--                  0   -> "000"  Y = "00000001" (Y0)
--                  5   -> "101"  Y = "00100000" (Y5)
--                  5   -> "101"  Y = "00100000" (Y5)
--                  3   -> "011"  Y = "00001000" (Y3)
--              All tested with EN=1 and EN=0.
